Load a speech encoder by trying several methods:
1. Using generic "load_model_ensemble_and_task" from fairseq;
2. Using the specific Wav2VecLaser class, if it is implemented in fairseq;
3. Using lower-leavel loading with patched config.
Return the model, its config, and its Fairseq task.

Merge the sorted input shards into one sorted output shard:
1. Open all the shards for read simultaneously;
2. In a loop, copy the line from the shard with the largest score;
3. When some input files are depleted, remove them.
This is always a non-parallel run (without sharding).

Compute and index embeddings for a language and add them to the Lang structure.
Parameter `orig_lang` is the name of the real language (e.g. "en"),
while `lang` is the name of the language shard (e.g. "en001")
